.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic shell that reads commands from the user and executes them. It supports simple commands without arguments, pipes, or redirections. The shell displays a prompt and waits for input, executing commands using execve.
.SH USAGE
Run in interactive mode:
.RS
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($) exit
.RE

Or in non-interactive mode:
.RS
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
None.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell exits with status 0 on success, or non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)
.SH AUTHORS
See AUTHORS file.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs to the project repository.